# Components Agent Notes

This folder contains reusable UI components grouped by domain (e.g., `common/`, `partner_request/`).

## Structure

Each component usually lives in its own folder:

- `<compName>.vue` â€” main component
- `<compName>.ts` â€” props/emits/types/helpers
- `<compName>.scss` â€” styles
- `<compName>.md` â€” component documentation

If a component name conflicts with a built-in element name, prefix it with `PU`.

## Vue component template

Use the standard pattern:

- default export with `name` and `options` (use `BasicComponentOptions` when applicable)
- `defineProps()` and `defineEmits()` from the componentâ€™s `.ts` module
- `defineModel()` for v-model when needed
- styles loaded via `style lang="scss" scoped src="./compName.scss"`

## Styling

- Use SCSS design tokens and mixins: `sys-var()`, `pu-font`, `pu-elevation`, `pu-icon`.
- Prefer UnoCSS for utility styles in templates.
- Only use UniApp tags (`<view>`, `<text>`, `<image>`).

## i18n

- Do not hard-code text; use `useTranslate()` and `dt()`.

## Docs

- Keep component docs concise and follow the template in `AGENTS.doc.md`.
